Vaughn Williams Classification

Source

VW Class Description
Ia Moderate Na Channel blockage + QT prolongation (= most arrhythmogenic)
Ib Mild Na channel blockade + QT shortening
Ic Marked Na blockade + No QT Effect
II Beta blockers
III K+ blockers -> ⬇ K+ efflux + QT prolongation (prolongs action potential)
IV Non-dihydropyridine CCBs (⬇ conduction velocity and slow AV node conduction) - useful for acute and chronic AF for ventricular rate control.

Amiodarone side effects:

Acute Chronic
CHB Lung fibrosis
QT prolongation -> Arrhythmias Steatohepatitis
Thrombophlebitis if given in peripheral vein Hypo / Hyperthyroidism
Photosensitive slate gray rash
Cataracts
Sensory and motor neuropathy

Amiodarone also inhibits peripheral T4 to T3 conversion.

Monitoring of patients taking amiodarone

  • TFT, LFT, U&E, CXR prior to treatment
  • TFT, LFT every 6 months

MS is short for "Multiple cerebro-spinal sclerosis".
[!INFO] Pathology of MS.

  • chronic T cell-mediated autoimmune disorder characterised by demyelination in the central nervous system with multiple plaques of demyelination found throughout the brain and spinal cord
  • ? Due to damage to the oligodendrocytes.
  • Demyelinated areas are replaced with scarring -> "Sclerosis"
    • These plaques are seen mainly in the white matter
  • Relapsing remitting disease is the most common form with acute attacks lasting 1-2 months with remissions.
  • Demyelination has a prediliction of cervical spinal cord, optic nerves, corpus callosum, cerebellar connections of the brainstem. (contrast with PML where spinal cord and optic nerves are spared)
  • Spasticity (see [[2020-NOV-BasicSciences#Spacticity Vs. Ridigity]] )
  • [[Ophthalmologic diseases#Optic neuritis|Optic neuritis]] : (classic presentation -> unilateral, moderate, painful vision loss with afferent pupillary defect and normal fundus examination.
  • Uhthoff phenomenon - symptoms worsen in high temperatures.
  • Lhermitte's sign - Electrical shock sensation running down the back when neck is flexed.
    • Incontinence: USS is essential to assess residual bladder volume to exclude overflow incontinence as oxybutinin may worsen symptoms if prescribed before USS assessment)
    • Baclofen: GABA receptor agonist which reduces muscle spasticity.
    • Fingolimod - sphongosine receptor modulator
      • beta interferon - considered to be not as efective.
      • glatiramer acetate - immune decoy - reduced relapse frequency and reduce development of new MRI lesions. Given Sub cut or IM.
  1. DVT after a flight: 3 to 6 months. Source

Mechanism of establishment of membrane potentials.

  1. Na - equilibrium potential: +60 mV
  2. K - Eq potential: -90 mV
    Since the actual membrane potential of the cell is not equal to the equilibrium potentials for Na and K, these ions are not in equilibrium. It therefore, takes energy in the form of ATP to maintain the resting membrane potential by constantly pumping 3 sodium out and 2 potassium in by the Na/K ATPase.
    K concentration inside the cells is around 150, outside 5.
Spacticity Vs. Ridigity

| Pyramidal lesion (eg. multiple sclerosis) | Extrapyramidal lesions (parkinson's) |
| Tone is higher in initial part of movement (clasp knife) | Same throughout range of movement |

Ivabradine is a selective If channel blocker and acts by reducing firing rate of pacemaker cells in the sinoatrial node, without affecting the duration of action potential. The reduction of heart rate causes a reduction of left ventricular end diastolic pressure and increases the time useful to coronary flow by a prolongation of the diastole. A body of evidence found that two drugs are useful in ischemic patients whether at rest or during exercise. In addition, they can be used in monotherapy or in association with other conventional anti-ischemic drugs
1. Mnemonic: NiKOrandil
2. Proably has mortality benefit : Source (IONA study)
3. Potassium channel activators dilate arterial smooth muscle.
4. Nicorandil has nitrate groups as well so it also dilates veins.
5. So arterial and venodilation exerts an antianginal effect.
6. Side effects: headache
